<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="middle-adj">middle <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'mɪdl/    美 /'mɪdl/  </p>
<p>[只用于名词前]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>中间 (部分) 的；中央的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I booked three seats in the middle row. 
我预订了中间那排的3个座位。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>in sb's middle twenties</strong>
在某人25岁左右时</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>中等的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a middle-income family 
中等收入家庭</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>It was a relief and I came to a sudden stop just in the middle on the road.  （2017 全国  改错）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. on → of  </p></div>